reviews.review_text: Ramp It Up OK, I reviewed the AUD of this show not too long ago and gave it 4 stars, saying that it really is a 4.5 star show.  Well, now that we have this entry of a fantastic Matrix of two great sources, I guess I'd step it up to 4.75 stars.  Fantastic high energy show with perhaps to "blow-your-mind" explosions, but it has that consistent groove that doesn't let up or slow down.  Phil and Jerry just dig in deep and have some fun here.  Most definitely worth a listen.  Thanks again to the magician that is Mr. Seamons

The sound Jesus this sounds good. Excellent matrix. I used to just go for the soundboards when available. That was my buzz for awhile. Now I'm finding the matrix tapes really sweet. This one is lovely. I've only gotten through 2 minutes of Peggy-O and I'm already compelled to write a review. just beautiful sound. I'll give it a five because there's nothing lacking. It's the quality I like and expect and the songs are great, played well. '79 has a nice warm sound.
